olive oil
2 Potato
1 Beetroot
½ Onion
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
1 packet Beef Rump
1 packet Baby Leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet garlic aioli

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato into bite-sized chunks. Cut beetroot into 1cm chunks. Cut onion (see ingredients) into wedges.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with garlic & herb seasoning and a pinch of salt, and toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 25-30 minutes.
• When the veggies have 15 minutes cook time remaining, add peeled pumpkin pieces to the tray and cook until tender.

TIP: Beetroot stays firm when cooked. It's done when you can pierce with a fork.
Little cooks: Help toss the veggies!

• Meanwhile, place beefrump between two sheets of baking paper. Pound beef with a meat mallet or rolling pin until slightly flattened.
• Season beef with salt and generously with pepper.

TIP: Pounding the beef ensures that it's extra tender once cooked.

• When veggies have 10 minutes remaining, heat a large frying pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook beef, turning, for 5-6 minutes (depending on thickness), or until cooked to your liking. Transfer to a plate to rest.
• When the veggies are done, add baby leaves and a drizzle of white wine vinegar to the tray and gently toss to combine.

• Thinly slice beef.
• Divide roast veggie toss between plates. Top with beef rump.
• Serve with garlic aioli. Enjoy!